      <akn:section eId="sec_44_1002_02">
        <akn:num>44-1002.02</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Grounds for receivership.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The facility is unlawfully operating without a current District license;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The licensee has abandoned the facility;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_3">
      <akn:num>(3)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The facility is closing within 30 calendar days and cannot offer verifiable evidence that adequate arrangements, designed to minimize transfer trauma, have been made to relocate its residents;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_4">
      <akn:num>(4)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A condition or practice in the facility poses a serious, widespread danger, either immediate or recurring, to the health, safety, or welfare of the residents;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_5">
      <akn:num>(5)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Violations of residents’ rights, established pursuant to § 44-504(a)(4), are chronic, substantial, and widespread;</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_6">
      <akn:num>(6)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Insolvency of an owner or the licensee has placed the continued operation of the facility in serious jeopardy; or</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1002_02_7">
      <akn:num>(7)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The facility has been issued a restricted or provisional license by the Department of Health.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
